"content": "<h2>Flat, open baskets to carry bread</h2>\n<h3>In the chief baker's dream</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen40:16-Gen40:18\">GEN 40:16–40:18</a></p>\n<h3>For offering unleavened bread</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:23\">EXO 29:23</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:26\">LEV 8:26</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:2-Exod29:3\">EXO 29:2–29:3</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:1-Lev8:2\">LEV 8:1–8:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:15-Num6:17\">NUM 6:15–6:17</a></p>\n<h2>Baskets used to hold food</h2>\n<h3>To store household provisions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:5\">DEU 28:5</a></strong> <em>Signifying the continued provision of food for the household.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:17\">DEU 28:17</a></p>\n<h3>To collect food</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:20\">MAT 14:20</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:43\">MRK 6:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:17\">LUK 9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:13\">JHN 6:13</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:48\">MAT 13:48</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:37\">MAT 15:37</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:8\">MRK 8:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:9-Matt16:10\">MAT 16:9–16:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:19-Mark8:20\">MRK 8:19–8:20</a></p>\n<h2>Baskets used to carry fruit</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer24:1-Jer24:2\">JER 24:1–24:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:24\">DEU 23:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps81:6\">PSA 81:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:1-Amos8:2\">AMO 8:1–8:2</a></p>\n<h2>Other uses of baskets</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:3-Exod2:5\">EXO 2:3–2:5</a> <em>Moses is put into a papyrus basket</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut26:2-Deut26:4\">DEU 26:2–26:4</a> <em>firstfruits presented in a basket</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs10:7\">2KI 10:7</a> <em>the heads of Ahab's sons sent to Jehu in baskets</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech5:6-Zech5:11\">ZEC 5:6–5:11</a> <em>The wickedness of Jerusalem is removed, figuratively, to Babylon in a basket.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:25\">ACT 9:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:33\">2CO 11:33</a></p>",
